text:

You could be about to win an eye-watering amount of money.
Tonight's Euromillions draw has a £68million jackpot up for grabs. It's almost too much money.
Tonight's winning numbers will be published in the blog below as soon as we have them.
Having these millions in your back account would Brexit-proof you and your family and as many of your friends as you want.
Just think what a change the fortune would make to your life.
What are the chances of winning the lottery? Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
Mortgage worries most likely over, you could have your dream holiday this autumn, as well as a dream holiday in winter, spring and summer for as long as you want.
You'd live like a business magnate, film star or world class footballer - but without the publicity (unless you chose to go public).
Playing EuroMillions also means automatic entry into the UK Millionaire Maker. James Evans, 30, and his partner JoJo Smith, 28, from Romney Marsh in Kent, celebrate their £3 million National Lottery Scratchcard win
Players of the game choose five numbers from 1 to 50 and two lucky stars from 1 to 12.
You can also do a lucky dip.
EuroMillions is played in nine European countries and has two draws a week - one on Tuesday and one on Friday - with jackpots sometimes reaching into the hundreds of millions of pounds in the event of a multiple-rollover.
Euromillions was first drawn in February 2004 and initially only included the UK, France and Spain – before lottery organisers Ireland, Belgium, Luxembourg, Switzerland, Austria and Portugal joined in October that year. Days until Christmas
